McAlister v. The Town of Eastman. Neither the bill of exceptions nor the brief for the plaintiff in error being signed by him or by any attorney of this court, and there being no appearance by any one in person to prosecute, and the costs not being paid or tendered, the writ of error is April 17, 1893.

Argued at the last term.

W. B. Coeeee, by brief, for plaintiff in error. E. A. Smith, contra.

Dismissed.
